  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensure that the environment and the natural resources upon which human lives and livelihoods depend are managed in ways that sustain productivity growth, a healthy population, as well as the intrinsic spiritual and cultural value of the environment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Environment - General is used when Environment sectors are unknown or foreign assistance is allocated to multiple sectors within this category.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Veracruz coast is one of the most important waterfowl and shorebird continental migratory routes. However, extensive cattle grazing and forest fires threaten this wetland complex, especially its mangroves. Over the last 24 years approximately 12,000 acres of mangroves have been lost, and more than 56,000 wetland acres have been turned into grasslands. This project, with the help and involvement of locals, seeks to mitigate the destructive processes and to restore the wetland system to benefit habitat for the conservation of migratory birds The project will be implemented in the 715,175 acre Alvarado Wetland Complex (ALS). It provides habitat to at least 346 bird species, including Snowy Plover, Red Knot Green-winged Teal, American Golden Plover, Wilson&#x2019;s Plover, and Wilson&#x2019;s Phalarope. The project will protect 15,355 acres of wetlands through a variety of legal mechanisms; and develop an online training platform for a certificate program in mangrove restoration and sustainable use. Forty-five students will receive training in the first year of operation.. The project will: 1) protect 15,355 acres of wetlands through a variety of legal mechanisms; and, 2) develop an online training platform for a certificate program in mangrove restoration and sustainable use. Forty-five students will receive training in the first year of operation.. conservation agreements on 450 acres (350 wetland acres and 100 upland acres). Enhancement activities will take place on 250 wetland acres,</narrative>
  </description>
